Package: xiacf
Type: Package
Title: Quantifying Nonlinear Dependence and Lead-Lag Dynamics via Chatterjee's Xi
Version: 0.4.0.9000
Authors@R: person(given = "Yasunori", family = "Watanabe",
                  role = c("aut", "cre"),
                  email = "watanabe.yasunori@outlook.com")
Maintainer: Yasunori Watanabe <watanabe.yasunori@outlook.com>
Description: Implements a robust framework for detecting non-linear dependence 
    and directional lead-lag relationships in time series data. Utilizing 
    Chatterjee's rank correlation (Xi), it provides tools for univariate (Xi-ACF), 
    bivariate (Xi-CCF), and multivariate network (xi_matrix) analyses. 
    Features include rigorous hypothesis testing with dynamic significance levels 
    via IAAFT and MIAAFT surrogate data generation algorithms, bidirectional 
    lead-lag evaluation, and parallelized rolling window analysis for detecting 
    structural breaks. Core computations are highly optimized in C++ using 'RcppArmadillo'.
